HEADWORD: Expressure
<hw>Ex*pres"sure</hw> <pr>(?;135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
expressing; expression; utterance; representation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An operation more divine⟦br⟧
Than breath or pen can give <qex>expressure</qex> to.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exprobrate</ent>⟦br⟧
